8 Theme Cruises to Book in 2025

Looking for a cruise that matches your interests? Check out these 8 incredible theme cruises in 2025, featuring exclusive events, celebrity guests, and immersive experiences at sea.

By Cruise Booking Team
Updated on: April 10, 2025
Share this on:

Cruising in 2025 is more exciting than ever, with theme cruises catering to every passion—from music and food to wellness and adventure. Whether you're a film buff, a history enthusiast, or a fitness fanatic, there's a perfect voyage waiting for you. These specially curated cruises offer unique experiences, exclusive events, and the chance to connect with like-minded travelers. If you're looking to turn your next vacation into an immersive adventure, check out these eight incredible theme cruises to book in 2025.

Top Theme Cruises in 2025

Ready to cruise with a purpose? Here are eight incredible theme cruises to book this year.

In This Article
  1. The Old School Cruise: A Must for Music Fans
  2. Christmas On the Rhine: A Festive Wonderland for Holiday Enthusiasts
  3. Literature Festival at Sea: A Dream Voyage for Book Lovers
  4. Chefs Making Waves: A Foodie’s Dream at Sea
  5. 2025 British Isles Golf Cruise: A Golf Enthusiast's Paradise
  6. Celebration of Wellness: A Rejuvenating River Journey
  7. Rome & Prix du Monde of Monaco: The Ultimate Getaway for Racing Fanatics
  8. Halloween on the High Seas: A Spooky Adventure for Families

The Old School Cruise: A Must for Music Fans

Photo Courtesy: Norwegian Cruise Line

Step back in time and groove to legendary hits aboard The Old School Cruise, an electrifying music festival at sea. Setting sail from San Pedro, California, from May 2-5, 2025, this cruise promises an unforgettable weekend filled with iconic performances by The S.O.S. Band, The Manhattans, Zapp, Stevie B, Sister Sledge, and more. Hosted on the Carnival Radiance, guests can enjoy unlimited dining, thrilling casino nights, poolside relaxation, comedy shows, and interactive games, all while soaking in the nostalgia of classic tunes.

This all-inclusive experience covers concerts, specialty dining, and access to exclusive entertainment, ensuring nonstop fun from the moment you board. With a stop in Ensenada, Mexico, expect a mix of music, adventure, and relaxation. If you love old-school jams and high-energy performances, this cruise is your ultimate getaway.

Christmas On the Rhine: A Festive Wonderland for Holiday Enthusiasts

Photo Courtesy: Viking Cruises

Step into a winter fairy tale with Christmas on the Rhine, an enchanting Viking River Cruise that sails between Amsterdam and Basel, Switzerland, with stops in Germany, the Netherlands, and France. Offered throughout November and December 2025, this eight-day voyage immerses guests in the magic of Europe’s most charming Christmas markets, where twinkling lights, handcrafted gifts, and aromatic glühwein set the scene for a truly festive getaway.

Wander through Cologne’s lively holiday markets, sip Weihnachtsbier in Rüdesheim, and indulge in Alsatian delicacies in Strasbourg. The journey also offers scenic cruises past hilltop castles along the UNESCO-listed Middle Rhine, plus stops at historic cities like Dordrecht, Koblenz, and Speyer. Whether you’re browsing for unique gifts, savoring seasonal treats, or admiring snow-dusted landscapes, this river cruise is the ultimate holiday escape.

Literature Festival at Sea: A Dream Voyage for Book Lovers

Photo Courtesy: Cunard Line

Set sail on a journey of words and wisdom aboard Cunard’s Queen Mary 2, as the Literature Festival at Sea transforms this transatlantic crossing into a haven for book enthusiasts. From December 8–15, 2025, this oceanic book festival, hosted in partnership with The Times and The Sunday Times Cheltenham Literature Festival, brings together renowned authors, historians, journalists, and literary critics for an immersive experience at sea.

Expect riveting discussions, book signings, Q&A sessions, and masterclasses from literary icons, including journalist Sophie Raworth and broadcaster Richard Coles, with more special guests. Whether you're a devoted reader or an aspiring writer, you can engage in writing workshops, explore thought-provoking panels, and gain insights into an author’s creative process. Beyond the literary excitement, enjoy Cunard’s signature luxuries, from world-class dining to relaxing spa treatments, making this voyage a perfect blend of intellect and indulgence.

Chefs Making Waves: A Foodie’s Dream at Sea

Photo Courtesy: Norwegian Cruise Line

Dive into a gastronomic adventure aboard the Norwegian Gem from May 5–9, 2025, as Chefs Making Waves brings together some of the most celebrated names in the culinary world. This four-night voyage from Miami to Cozumel, Mexico, features award-winning chefs such as Richard Blais, Nyesha Arrington, Scott Conant, Maneet Chauhan, and more, who will host cooking demonstrations, masterclasses, and curated culinary panels for food enthusiasts.

The true highlight? Exclusive, multi-course dining experiences designed by renowned chef pairings, offering a unique menu each night. Guests can also enjoy mixology sessions, theme nights, and lively onboard entertainment, all complemented by a Premium Plus Beverage Package for an indulgent, all-inclusive experience. In Cozumel, explore the island’s stunning beaches, vibrant local markets, and world-class diving spots before returning to the ship for another evening of gourmet delights.

2025 British Isles Golf Cruise: A Golf Enthusiast's Paradise

Photo Courtesy: Azamara Cruises

Tee off on the ultimate golf adventure with Azamara’s 13-night British Isles Golf Cruise, in partnership with PerryGolf, setting sail in mid-July 2025. This exclusive itinerary not only features six rounds at world-class courses across the British Isles but also includes attendance at the prestigious 153rd Open at Royal Portrush in Northern Ireland—a bucket-list event for golf enthusiasts.

Sailing aboard the Azamara Journey, the voyage begins in Southampton and makes stops in Dublin, Belfast, Liverpool, and multiple destinations in Scotland, concluding with three days in Edinburgh. Golfers will enjoy VIP access to top-tier courses, on-course lunches, green fees,and clubhouse drinks, while non-golfers can explore cities through brewery tours, sightseeing excursions, and river cruises. With four overnight stays and luxurious onboard amenities—including gourmet dining, spa treatments, and Azamara’s renowned AzAmazing Evenings—this cruise blends the love of golf with an unforgettable cultural experience.

Celebration of Wellness: A Rejuvenating River Journey

Photo Courtesy: AmaWaterways

Step off into a wellness-focused escape with AmaWaterways’ Celebration of Wellness cruise, a seven-night voyage from Budapest to Vilshofen, departing August 2, 2025. Designed for travelers prioritizing mental and physical well-being, this immersive experience features daily yoga, stretching, dance, and core-strengthening classes, as well as guided hikes, bike tours, and runs at each port.

The itinerary includes stops in Vienna, Weissenkirchen, Bratislava, Linz, and Passau, with each destination offering active excursions and cultural exploration. Onboard, guests can indulge in nutrient-rich gourmet meals, a morning juice bar, wellness talks, and expert-led workshops. Whether enjoying Champagne Yoga at sunrise, a refreshing dip in the sun-deck pool, or an evening dance session, this cruise blends relaxation, fitness, and mindful living for the ultimate rejuvenating getaway.

Rome & Prix du Monde of Monaco: The Ultimate Getaway for Racing Fanatics

Photo Courtesy: MSC Cruises

Set sail on Windstar Cruises’ Wind Surf, the world’s largest sailing yacht, for an unparalleled Formula One experience from May 20-27, 2025. This exclusive voyage from Barcelona to Rome offers front-row access to the legendary Prix du Monde of Monaco, with two days of time trials and racing from a premier grandstand seat in Monte Carlo. Guests receive a Formula One-themed gift package, including binoculars, earplugs, and a seat cushion, ensuring maximum comfort while soaking in the high-speed action.

Beyond the track, enjoy private Prix du Monde events, including a cocktail reception and dinner, all hosted by a Formula One expert providing exclusive insights. The luxurious itinerary includes stops in Palamós, Sanary-sur-Mer, Cannes, Monte Carlo (overnight), Portoferraio, and Rome, offering time to explore elite boutiques, stroll glamorous promenades, and unwind on the world-famous beaches of the Rivieras. For motorsport fans and luxury travelers alike, this sailing delivers the ultimate Grand Prix getaway.

Halloween on the High Seas: A Spooky Adventure for Families

Photo Courtesy: Seabourn

Disney Cruise Line’s Halloween on the High Seas brings a whimsical and family-friendly take on Halloween, perfect for travelers with children and Disney fans of all ages. Available on Disney Magic, Disney Fantasy, Disney Dream, and Disney Wish, these special sailings run between late September and October 31, transforming the ships with festive décor, themed entertainment, and costumed Disney characters.

This spellbinding experience features Mickey’s Mouse-querade, trick-or-treating, Halloween-themed arts and crafts, and exclusive character meet-and-greets with Disney favorites in ghostly attire. Passengers can also enjoy seasonal treats, enchanting performances, and plenty of eerie yet delightful surprises. With a fun, lighthearted atmosphere, this cruise is an excellent way to celebrate Halloween at sea without the scares.

Conclusion

With an exciting lineup of theme cruises in 2025, there’s something for every kind of traveler—whether you’re passionate about music, literature, fine dining, wellness, or adventure. These specially curated sailings go beyond traditional cruising, offering immersive experiences, exclusive events, and the chance to connect with like-minded enthusiasts. Whether you're dancing to classic hits, teeing off at legendary golf courses, exploring festive Christmas markets, or indulging in gourmet delights, these voyages make for unforgettable getaways. Book your ideal theme cruise with CruiseBooking.com now and set off on a journey tailored to your passions.
